00:14:23.020 --> 00:14:25.860
like disease, pregnancy, regret --

00:14:26.460 --> 00:14:28.236
more positive outcomes

00:14:28.260 --> 00:14:30.676
like being able to communicate
with their partner,

00:14:30.700 --> 00:14:32.396
who they said they knew very well;

00:14:32.420 --> 00:14:34.996
preparing for the experience responsibly;

00:14:35.020 --> 00:14:36.580
enjoying themselves.

00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:38.700
What was their secret?

00:14:39.540 --> 00:14:43.796
The Dutch girls said
that their doctors, teachers and parents

00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:45.436
talked to them candidly,

00:14:45.460 --> 00:14:47.196
from an early age,

00:14:47.220 --> 00:14:52.140
about sex, pleasure
and the importance of mutual trust.

00:14:53.300 --> 00:14:54.516
What's more,

00:14:54.540 --> 00:14:59.316
while American parents weren't necessarily
less comfortable talking about sex,

00:14:59.340 --> 00:15:01.836
we tend to frame those conversations

00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:05.460
entirely in terms or risk and danger,

00:15:06.420 --> 00:15:11.100
whereas Dutch parents talk
about balancing responsibility and joy.

00:15:12.020 --> 00:15:13.236
I have to tell you,

00:15:13.260 --> 00:15:15.116
as a parent myself,

00:15:15.140 --> 00:15:17.196
that hit me hard,

00:15:17.220 --> 00:15:19.756
because I know,

00:15:19.780 --> 00:15:22.036
had I not delved into that research,

00:15:22.060 --> 00:15:25.836
I would have talked to my own child
about contraception,

00:15:25.860 --> 00:15:27.716
about disease protection,

00:15:27.740 --> 00:15:30.476
about consent because I'm a modern parent,

00:15:30.500 --> 00:15:31.834
and I would have thought ...

00:15:33.820 --> 00:15:35.020
job well done.

00:15:36.140 --> 00:15:38.420
Now I know that's not enough.

00:15:39.740 --> 00:15:42.780
I also know what I hope for for our girls.

00:15:43.780 --> 00:15:48.036
I want them to see sexuality
as a source of self-knowledge,

00:15:48.060 --> 00:15:50.276
creativity and communication,

00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:52.916
despite its potential risks.

00:15:52.940 --> 00:15:56.396
I want them to be able
to revel in their bodies' sensuality

00:15:56.420 --> 00:15:57.940
without being reduced to it.

00:15:58.940 --> 00:16:02.156
I want them to be able
to ask for what they want in bed,

00:16:02.180 --> 00:16:03.420
and to get it.

00:16:04.380 --> 00:16:07.836
I want them to be safe
from unwanted pregnancy,

00:16:07.860 --> 00:16:09.076
disease,

00:16:09.100 --> 00:16:10.316
cruelty,

00:16:10.340 --> 00:16:11.916
dehumanization,

00:16:11.940 --> 00:16:13.140
violence.

00:16:13.900 --> 00:16:15.676
If they are assaulted,

00:16:15.700 --> 00:16:19.156
I want them to have recourse
from their schools,

00:16:19.180 --> 00:16:20.596
their employers,

00:16:20.620 --> 00:16:21.820
the courts.

00:16:22.940 --> 00:16:24.340
It's a lot to ask,

00:16:25.060 --> 00:16:26.260
but it's not too much.

00:16:27.300 --> 00:16:31.356
As parents, teachers,
advocates and activists,

00:16:31.380 --> 00:16:36.156
we have raised a generation
of girls to have a voice,

00:16:36.180 --> 00:16:40.036
to expect egalitarian
treatment in the home,

00:16:40.060 --> 00:16:41.316
in the classroom,

00:16:41.340 --> 00:16:42.540
in the workplace.

00:16:43.540 --> 00:16:48.196
Now it's time to demand
that intimate justice

00:16:48.220 --> 00:16:50.380
in their personal lives as well.

00:16:51.580 --> 00:16:52.796
Thank you.

00:16:52.820 --> 00:16:55.420
(Applause)

